OL,3,CFormer Reform leader in Wales admits
OL,4,Cbribery charges over pro-Russian
OL,5,Cstatements
OL,7,FThe former leader of Reform UK in
OL,8,FWales has pleaded guilty to bribery
OL,9,Fcharges relating to statements in
OL,10,Ffavour of Russia in the European
OL,11,FParliament.
OL,13,FOn Friday, Nathan Gill, 52, of
OL,14,FAnglesey, North Wales, admitted eight
OL,15,Fcounts of bribery on dates between
OL,16,FDecember 6 2018 and July 18 2019.
