OL,3,CFormer Reform leader in Wales admits
OL,4,Cbribery charges over pro-Russian
OL,5,Cstatements
OL,7,FThe charges stated that as an elected
OL,8,Fmember of the European Parliament for
OL,9,Fthe constituency of Wales in the UK,
OL,10,Fhe "agreed to receive financial
OL,11,Fadvantage, namely money", which
OL,12,Fconstituted "the improper performance"
OL,13,Fas the holder of an elected office.
OL,15,FIt has been alleged he made statements
OL,16,Fin the European Parliament and in
OL,17,Fopinion pieces to news outlets, such
OL,18,Fas 112 Ukraine, which were "supportive
OL,19,Fof a particular narrative" which would
OL,20,F"benefit Russia regarding events in
OL,21,FUkraine".
