OL,3,CFormer Reform leader in Wales admits
OL,4,Cbribery charges over pro-Russian
OL,5,Cstatements
OL,7,FThat charge alleged Gill conspired
OL,8,Fwith Voloshyn and "others" between
OL,9,FJanuary 1 2018 and February 1 2020,
OL,10,Fand that he accepted "quantities of
OL,11,Fmoney in cash" which was "improper
OL,12,Fperformance by him of his function or
OL,13,Factivity as the holder" of a position
OL,14,Fin the European Parliament.
OL,16,FProsecutor Mark Heywood KC said the
OL,17,Fguilty pleas were "satisfactory"
OL,18,Fbecause the bribery charges reflected
OL,19,Fthe criminal activities.
